<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-150-093 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 765 605</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 21 1991 n1680* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple may cut 1,000 or more jobs in effort to cut costs $400m.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Layoffs).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   System 7.0 (Operating system) (Usage)Apple Macintosh Classic (Microcomputer) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     LayoffMarket ShareOperating SystemsUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>APPLE MAY CUT 1,000 OR MORE JOBS IN EFFORT TO CUT COSTS $400mandM;Faced with a squeeze on margins as it successfully bids for market share withits new low-cost Macintoshes, Apple Computer Inc is not discouragingspeculation that a major lay-off may be on the way.andP;  According to AssociatedPress, Apple may be considering a reduction in its 15,400-strong payroll ofas many as 2,000 people, 12% of the total.andP;  The company privatelyacknowledges that it may make cuts of 1,000 or more as it tries to cut itsoperating costs by $400m a year.andP;  It is also expected to put its low-endMacintoshes through some of the no-frills computer superstores spring up inthe US.At its developers conference last week, Apple Computer Inc said itwould be bringing out a 68030-based version of the bottom end MacintoshClassic - the current Classic uses the 16-bit 68000 microprocessor, and saidthat all new Macintoshes would run only the System 7 version of the operatingsystem, increasing the pressure on third party software developers to upgradetheir applications to System 7.andP;  The company also confirmed that the TowerMacintosh will use the 68040 chip and will include 24-bit colour support andEthernet support on the processor board.andP;  And according to Microbytes Daily,the company's Advanced Technology Group showed off a working prototype of apalmtop computer.andP;  The machine had a notebook-like visual interface thatflipped pages when a hand was swiped along the screen surface.andP;  Objects andoperations were activated using a pen, but the machine could also becontrolled without extensive use of stylus.andO;</TEXT></DOC>